import matplotlib.dates as mdates

# Input field cleanup
df = dataset.copy()
df.columns = [''Date'', ''Current'', ''YOY'']
df[''Date''] = pd.to_datetime(df[''Date''])
df = df.sort_values(''Date'')

# Totals and percent change
total_current = df[''Current''].sum()
total_yoy = df[''YOY''].sum()
pct_change = ((total_current - total_yoy) / total_yoy) * 100 if total_yoy else 0

ax.plot(df[''Date''], df[''Current''], color="#2CA995", linewidth=2)

# Remove axis clutter
ax.set_xlim(df[''Date''].min(), df[''Date''].max())
ax.set_ylim(0, max(df[''Current''].max(), total_current) * 0.3)
ax.axis(''off'')

# Chart title at top center
fig.text(0.7, 0.95, "Assignments Worked", ha=''right'', va=''top'', fontsize=48, fontweight=''medium'')

# KPI Callout in center

        transform=ax.transAxes, ha=''right'', va=''top'',
        fontsize=70, fontweight=''regular'', color=''black'')

# YOY % just below it
ax.text(0.5, 0.40, f"{arrow} {abs(pct_change):.0f}% vs last year",
        transform=ax.transAxes, ha=''left'', va=''top'',
        fontsize=32, fontweight=''normal'', color=color)

# Adjust layout to use full space
plt.subplots_adjust(left=0, right=1, top=1, bottom=0)

plt.show()

from matplotlib.patches import Polygon, Rectangle
import math

# ---------- SETTINGS ----------
total_height = 1.0  # Total funnel height

custom_colors = [
    ''#955706'',
    ''#BF7B22'',
    ''#E99B34'',
    ''#FCD096'',
    ''#FFE6C3''

total_value = values.sum()

slope = 0.4  # same angle for first two trapeziums

shapes.append((''trapezium'', top_width, bw1, h1))

bw3 = top_width - 2 * steep_slope * h3
